    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "D&C",
        "delineation": "Section",
        "number": 110,
        "summary": "1\u201310, The Lord Jehovah appears in glory and accepts the Kirtland Temple as His house; 11\u201312, Moses and Elias each appear and commit their keys and dispensations; 13\u201316, Elijah returns and commits the keys of his dispensation as promised by Malachi.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The veil was taken from our minds, and the eyes of our understanding were opened.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Veil.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 76:12 (10, 12, 19); 136:32; 138:11.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "We saw the Lord standing upon the breastwork of the pulpit, before us; and under his feet was a paved work of pure gold, in color like amber.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Privilege of Seeing; Jesus Christ, Appearances, Postmortal.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 3:10; 1\u00a0Ne. 1:11 (8\u201315); JS\u2014H 1:17.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 1:27 (26\u201328); Rev. 21:21; D&C 137:4.",
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 119
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "His eyes were as a flame of fire; the hair of his head was white like the pure snow; his countenance shone above the brightness of the sun; and his voice was as the sound of the rushing of great waters, even the voice of Jehovah, saying:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 1:14; 2:18. TG\u00a0God, Body of, Corporeal Nature.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 34:29 (29\u201335); Rev. 1:16; Hel. 5:36; JS\u2014H 1:32.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 100
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 1:24; 43:2; Rev. 1:15; D&C 133:22.",
                        "start": 148,
                        "end": 153
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Jehovah.",
                        "start": 221,
                        "end": 228
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I am the first and the last; I am he who liveth, I am he who was slain; I am your advocate with the Father.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Firstborn.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 5:24 (22\u201324); Zech. 13:6; D&C 45:52 (51\u201352).",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Access to; Jesus Christ, Authority of; Jesus Christ, Relationships with the Father.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, your sins are forgiven you; you are clean before me; therefore, lift up your heads and rejoice.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 5:21. TG\u00a0Forgive.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Joy.",
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 229
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let the hearts of your brethren rejoice, and let the hearts of all my people rejoice, who have, with their might, built this house to my name.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 109:4 (4\u20135).",
                        "start": 114,
                        "end": 119
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For behold, I have accepted this house, and my name shall be here; and I will manifest myself to my people in mercy in this house.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Chr. 7:16. TG\u00a0Dedication.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Temple.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Manifestations of.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, I will appear unto my servants, and speak unto them with mine own voice, if my people will keep my commandments, and do not pollute this holy house.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 19:11 (10\u201311); D&C 50:45.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 88:134; 97:15 (15\u201317). TG\u00a0Pollution.",
                        "start": 129,
                        "end": 136
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holiness.",
                        "start": 142,
                        "end": 152
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea the hearts of thousands and tens of thousands shall greatly rejoice in consequence of the blessings which shall be poured out, and the endowment with which my servants have been endowed in this house.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 12:3 (1\u20133); D&C 39:15; Abr. 2:11 (8\u201311).",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 103
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 95:8 (8\u20139).",
                        "start": 139,
                        "end": 148
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the fame of this house shall spread to foreign lands; and this is the beginning of the blessing which shall be poured out upon the heads of my people. Even so. Amen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zech. 12:10; D&C 105:12.",
                        "start": 115,
                        "end": 121
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "After this vision closed, the heavens were again opened unto us; and Moses appeared before us, and committed unto us the keys of the gathering of Israel from the four parts of the earth, and the leading of the ten tribes from the land of the north.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Vision.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 1:1.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 17:3; D&C 133:55.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 74
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 113:6. TG\u00a0Priesthood, Keys of.",
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 125
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 22:12 (10\u201312); Jacob 6:2; D&C 29:7; 45:43; 127:6. TG\u00a0Israel, Gathering of.",
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 142
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 133:26. TG\u00a0Israel, Ten Lost Tribes of.",
                        "start": 242,
                        "end": 247
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "After this, Elias appeared, and committed the dispensation of the gospel of Abraham, saying that in us and our seed all generations after us should be blessed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "BD\u00a0Elias.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Dispensations.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gal. 3:8 (6\u201329); D&C 124:58. TG\u00a0Abrahamic Covenant.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 18:18 (17\u201319).",
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 131
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mission of Latter-day Saints.",
                        "start": 151,
                        "end": 158
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "After this vision had closed, another great and glorious vision burst upon us; for Elijah the prophet, who was taken to heaven without tasting death, stood before us, and said:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Vision.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 17:1; Mal. 4:5 (5\u20136); Matt. 17:3 (1\u20134); Luke 4:25; 3\u00a0Ne. 25:5 (5\u20136); D&C 2:1; 35:4; 128:17; 138:46. TG\u00a0Translated Beings.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, the time has fully come, which was spoken of by the mouth of Malachi\u2014testifying that he [Elijah] should be sent, before the great and dreadful day of the Lord come\u2014",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To turn the hearts of the fathers to the children, and the children to the fathers, lest the whole earth be smitten with a curse\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JS\u2014H 1:39 (38\u201339).",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Love within; Genealogy and Temple Work; Salvation for the Dead.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore, the keys of this dispensation are committed into your hands; and by this ye may know that the great and dreadful day of the Lord is near, even at the doors.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Authority; Priesthood, Keys of; Sealing.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Dispensations; Restoration of the Gospel.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zeph. 1:14. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Second Coming; Last Days.",
                        "start": 124,
                        "end": 127
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}